race.comment: EXUBERANCE (2) progressed nicely last time out at the second run of the campaign when she did her best work late and finished 2.5 lengths from the winner in second over 1000m at Ballarat. Stepping up a level this time but on her best form she is one of the chief contenders. AUDIO POP CAM (10) got her career off to the perfect start with a nice maiden win at Pakenham and was then tested at city level, where she didn't run up to her best. Put away after that and has jumped out nicely since. HEDONIST (1) finished fifth over 1100m at Warrnambool at his most recent appearance on April 29. Sure to make his presence felt. MY ZEPHYR (12) turned in a strong performance first-up when in the money at Murray Bridge but disappointed last time when eighth, beaten 1.75 lengths, at Warrnambool over 1200m. Nicely placed to make amends.
